# Chapter 2 – Network Configuration

## Objective

The objective of this chapter was to configure the network infrastructure for the SOC Detection and Monitoring Lab. A properly configured network is essential for enabling communication between the attacker, victim, and SIEM, allowing attack simulations, log collection, and security monitoring.

---

## Lab Network Overview

The SOC lab consists of three virtual machines connected using Oracle VirtualBox.

| Virtual Machine | Role | IP Address |
|----------------|------|------------|
| Ubuntu Server | Splunk Enterprise (SIEM) | 10.10.10.4 |
| Kali Linux | Attacker | 10.10.10.5 |
| Windows 10 | Victim | 10.10.10.6 |

The virtual machines were connected using a **VirtualBox NAT Network**, allowing communication between the systems while providing internet access through the host machine's network connection.

